@author Will Papper and Syndicate Inc.
 @title SPV management contract
@notice Only proceed if the msg.sender is the current manager
@notice Only proceed if the SPV is open
@notice Only proceed if the SPV is closed
@notice Only proceed if distributions have not been enabled
@notice Only proceed after distributions have been enabled
@notice Only proceed if the allowlist is enabled
@notice Only proceed if the allowlist is disabled

@notice Only proceed if the LP attests that they are an accredited
 investor
@dev This check should always occur before checking if the SPV is open or closed

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Syndicate profit share must be greater than or equal to 300 (0.30%)"

documentation.text: @notice Allowing addresses is unnecessary if you pass in setAutoConfirmDeposit(true)

@notice All addresses are denied by default, so this is only necessary if
 you want to remove a previously allowed address

@dev Manager fees can only be set higher while the SPV is open to prevent
 managers from changing fees on LPs without the ability to act on those
 fee changes. The manager can only change fees while LPs still have the
 ability to pull their money out. After that point, fees can only be
 lowered and not raised.

@dev The manager can burn the fees or send them to an address that they
 do not own if they'd like, there is no requirement that the
 managerFeeAddress cannot equal address(0) or e.g. the address of a
 charity

@notice Close an SPV to new deposits. An SPV must be closed before
 distributions can be redeemed.
 @notice Once an SPV is closed, it cannot be opened again. This is to
 prevent issues with redeeming distributions interacting with new deposits
 (e.g. a user with a 10% stake performs a withdrawal, and then a deposit
 occurs that dilutes them down to a 1% stake. From that point onward, they
 would only be entitled to 1% of the distributions)
@notice Used by the pending manager to claim current manager status

params.totalDistributions: Total distributions available from the fund, claimed or not.  Make sure this matches the token type (primary or secondary) passed in for claimedDistributions.
params.userContributions: Total user has deposited to the fund

returns._0: Value in distributions that user is eligible to withdraw

params.profitShareNumerator: Establish fractional profit share (decimal %'s get messy fast). The profit share denominator is always PROFIT_SHARE_DENOMINATOR, which is set to 10000. Examples of different percentages can be found in the calculateProfitShare tests
params.withdrawal: Total amount to user is sending

returns._0: Tuple of (withdrawalToUser, withdrawalToProfitShare) The withdrawal that the user will receive and the amount of the profit share that the Syndicate treasury (or, if adapted to asset management, the Syndicate manager) will receive during withdrawal

createSPV(address,uint256,uint256,uint25.details: The rejectIfNotCurrentManager modifier is not necessary here since the SPV is being initialized and has not been created yetThis function is high risk. If a current SPV can be overwritten, someone could take control of the deposits by changing the current manager

params.allowlistEnabled: False allows contributions to be sent without the manager needing to allow them. The manager can always reject a contribution before an SPV closes with rejectLPInvestment()
params.closeDate: The date that the SPV will automatically close in UNIX time.
params.maxDeposit: The max deposit per wallet address.
params.maxTotalDeposits: The max deposit amount for the fund/SPV.
params.primaryERC20ContractAddress: The address of the ERC20 used for deposits (e.g. DAI or USDC's contract addresses) and withdrawals. Stablecoins are strongly recommended, especially for funds that are open for an extended period of time. (Otherwise one contributor might contribute one unit when a token is $100, and another contributor might contribute one unit when a token is $200, and they would have the same percentage ownership because they have both contributed one unit of a token. Stablecoins prevent this because the value is consistent.)
params.syndicateProfitSharePercent: The Syndicate profit share adjusted by PERCENT_MULTIPLE (set to 1000). For example, the minimum profit share of .30% should be passed in as 300 (since it is .30% * 1000). This means that the max precision is .001%

emitMemo(address,bytes32,bytes32).details: For more on the recommendation to use `blake2b-328` hashes, see https://medium.com/temporal-cloud/efficient-usable-and-cheap-storage-of-ipfs-hashes-in-solidity-smart-contracts-eb3bef129eba

getSPVLPInfo(address,address).details: This function **must** be kept up to date with the web3 UI when making changes. All PRs that change this function **must** be coordinated with an engineer on the Web3 Dashboard.

params.metadataKey: The string that is the key of the metadata to look up

getSPVValues(address).details: This function **must** be kept up to date with the web3 UI when making changes. All PRs that change this function **must** be coordinated with an engineer on the Web3 Dashboard.

lpInvestInSPV(address,uint256,bool).details: Consider removing the onlySPVOpen modifier since the processDeposit function has the same modifier, if you want to save on gas costs. Right now, the duplicate modifiers provide additional safety when developing at the cost of a small increase in gas.

params.accredited: Attestation that the LP is an accredited investor. Must be true to continue
params.amount: The amount of the investment (note that this is calculated using the primary ERC20 token)
params.spvAddress: The address that the LP is investing in

lpWithdrawFromSPV(address,address,uint25.details: Withdrawals are restricted to the primary or secondary ERC20 contract address. If we allowed any arbitrary ERC20 address, we would also need to track percentages for each arbitrary ERC20 address. This is significantly outside of the scope of the SPV contract and should be saved for future asset management contracts

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

setManagerFeeAddress(address,address).details: The manager can burn the fees or send them to an address that they do not own if they'd like, there is no requirement that the managerFeeAddress cannot equal address(0) or e.g. the address of a charity

setManagerFees(address,uint256,uint256).details: Manager fees can only be set higher while the SPV is open to prevent managers from changing fees on LPs without the ability to act on those fee changes. The manager can only change fees while LPs still have the ability to pull their money out. After that point, fees can only be lowered and not raised.

params.inactiveStatus: Pass in true to mark the SPV as inactive. False (the default value upon SPV initialization) marks the SPV as active.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

allowAddress(address,address).notice: Allowing addresses is unnecessary if you pass in setAutoConfirmDeposit(true)

allowMultipleAddresses(address,address[].notice: Allowing addresses is unnecessary if you pass in setAutoConfirmDeposit(true)

calculateEligibleWithdrawal(uint256,uint.notice: Calculates the maximum value in distribution tokens (in either primary or secondary ERC20) that an LP can withdraw based on their percentage ownership at the moment that the fund closed and the distributions that they have already received.

closeSPV(address).notice: Close an SPV to new deposits. An SPV must be closed before distributions can be redeemed.Once an SPV is closed, it cannot be opened again. This is to prevent issues with redeeming distributions interacting with new deposits (e.g. a user with a 10% stake performs a withdrawal, and then a deposit occurs that dilutes them down to a 1% stake. From that point onward, they would only be entitled to 1% of the distributions)

confirmPendingManager(address).notice: Used by the pending manager to claim current manager status

denyAddress(address,address).notice: All addresses are denied by default, so this is only necessary if you want to remove a previously allowed address

emitMemo(address,bytes32,bytes32).notice: Emit an event that references a memo stored as 64 byte hash. IPFS is recommended. If an IPFS hash is used, it must be `blake2b-328` so that it can be stored in 64 bytesThis can be used to store a fund thesis or describe a transaction that a fund manager made in their wallet. This provides transparency by notifying LPs of transactions and allowing them to verify the proper use of funds.

getSPVLPInfo(address,address).notice: Return the LP info for an SPV

getSPVMetadata(address,string).notice: Return the metadata for a given key within an SPV

getSPVValues(address).notice: Return the settings for an SPV

lpInvestInSPV(address,uint256,bool).notice: Allow an LP to invest in an SPV

lpWithdrawFromSPV(address,address,uint25.notice: Withdrawal options are different if the SPV is open or closed. If it is open, only the deposit ERC20 can be withdrawn. If it is closed and distributions are disabled, no ERC20s of any kind can be withdrawn. If it is closed and distributions are enabled, any ERC20 address can be withdrawn. Distributions can be enabled by setting a distribution for the first time.

pauseContract().notice: Emergency pause function that can only be triggered by the contract ownerIts purpose is to pause deposits and withdrawals. All other functions will work when paused

rejectLPInvestment(address,address).notice: This is only used when the allowlist is disabled. When an allowlist is enabled, LPs have already been pre-approved so there is no need to reject investments.

renounceOwnership().notice: Renounce ownership of the contractUnpause the contract before ownership is renounced, to ensure that deposits/withdrawals are not locked

setDistribution(address,address,uint256).notice: Mark a distribution as availableIf this function is called before distributions are enabled, it will automatically enable distributions. Once enabled, distributions cannot be disabled.After enabling distributions, the secondary ERC20 address cannot be changed

setPendingManager(address,address).notice: The current manager is pending until they claim the currentManager status. This ensures that the new current manager has control over their wallet and has also agreed to manage the fund.To reset a pendingManager request, just set the pendingManager to be address(0). This is the value that it is initialized at within the SingleSPV struct (it is the default value for all addresses)

setSPVInactiveStatus(address,bool).notice: Mark an SPV as inactive. This signals that the SPV is no longer in use. This only changes the UI that end users see and has no practical implementation. If you would like to shut down a SPV, you should close the SPV and enable distributions instead.

unPauseContract().notice: Emergency unpause function that can only be triggered by the contract ownerIts purpose is to unpause deposits and withdrawals. All other functions will work when paused
